; DOMAIN: graph-theory [CLOSED, derived 2026-07-24] ; Claim: in a flow network the maximum flow value equals the minimum cut capacity (max-flow min-cut). ; Structure: (network (nodes s t) (capacity c)) (flow f feasible) (cut (S T) s-in-S t-in-T). ; Result: max{|f|} = min{cap(S,T)}; a flow is maximal iff no augmenting path exists (residual graph). ; Minimal: feasibility + conservation + augmenting-path-saturation => value-capacity duality. ; Bridge: LP-duality instance — primal max-flow, dual min-cut; connects to optimal-transport as a network transport dual. (= (maxflow $net) (mincut $net))